  <abstract>Full-length black and white engraving of "J. C. Calhoun" (1782-1850). He is posed with a U.S. flag, a globe, and a table filled with papers and books. An inkwell and feather pen are set atop the papers. The three documents on the table are labeled "Strict Construction," "Free Trade," and "The Sovereignty of States."</abstract>
  <abstract>Calhoun was a U.S. Representative and U.S. Senator from South Carolina. He was a leader of the War Hawk faction that agitated for war with Great Britain. Calhoun served as Secretary of War during the War of 1812.</abstract>
